text: Jean-Marc Lefranc (born February 20, 1947 in Grandcamp-Maisy) was a member of the National Assembly of France from 2002 to 2012. He represented the Calvados department, and is a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. ==References== Category:1947 births Category:Living people Category:People from Calvados (department) Category:Politicians from Normandy Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:Deputies of the 12th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic
title: Jean-Marc Lefranc
